com.github.naoghuman.lib.logger.core

Interface Logger

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultLogger, LoggerFacade

    public interface Logger
    The Interface for the Class DefaultLogger.

    Over the facade LoggerFacade the developer access to the Implementation from the methods in this Interface.

    Author:
    Naoghuman
    See Also:
    DefaultLogger, LoggerFacade

    • Method Detail

      • deactivate

        void deactivate(Boolean deactivate)
        Alloweds the developer to decide if the Logger should log or not.
        Can be usefull during testing purpose.
        Parameters:
        deactivate - Boolean which defined if the Logger should log or not. TRUE if no logging desired, otherwise FALSE for logging.

      • debug

        void debug(Class clazz,
           String msg)
        Prints a specific message in debug-mode for the given Class if (deactive == FALSE) and (isDebugEnabled() == TRUE).
        Parameters:
        clazz - The Class for that the message should be printed.
        msg - The message which should be printed.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if clazz == NULL.
        NullPointerException - if msg == NULL.
        See Also:
        deactivate(java.lang.Boolean), Logger.isDebugEnabled()

      • define

        void define(org.apache.logging.log4j.Level level)
        Lets the developer define a log Level which will be used in the methods own(Class, String) and own(Class, String, Throwable). Default is Level.DEBUG.

        All levels are allowed expected Level.ALL and Level.OFF.

        Parameters:
        level - The Level which should be used.
        See Also:
        Level, own(Class, String), own(Class, String, Throwable)

      • message

        void message(char borderSign,
             int borderSignCount,
             String figlet)
        This will print a Figlet or normal message in the logfile.
        For example with LoggerFacade.getDefault().message('#', 70, figlet); following will print to the log-file:

        #####################################################################
        Here you will see your message.
        #####################################################################

        Have a look at http://www.lemoda.net/games/message/message-instant.html how to generate a message-message.

        Parameters:
        borderSign - The signsign represent an element from the border.
        borderSignCount - Define how much elements have the border.
        figlet - The figlet (or in normal format) message between the border.

      • own

        void own(Class clazz,
         String msg)
        Prints a specific message in the defined log Level mode when (deactive == FALSE) and (isLogModeEnabled() == TRUE). The developer can the log level define in the method define(Level). Default is that Level.DEBUG.
        Parameters:
        clazz - The Class for that the message should be printed.
        msg - The message which should be printed.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if clazz == NULL.
        NullPointerException - if msg == NULL.
        See Also:
        define(Level)
